The paper deals with the problem of influence maximization in social networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The paper discusses the importance of community structure in social networks for learning to influence, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-categories of social networks (cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC), data science (cs.DS), and machine learning (cs.LG).
